ass=m><span class=title> Re: Buffing</span><hr size=1> Hit points does help anyone, but when casting the them, you have to use a regent.  At my level(24), the regent I need cost me aroung 2 gp.  Casting this on group would cost me 1.2 plat per cycle.  This stuff adds up, since I don't loot, because I am always medding.  Only on a few occasions have I had another group player give me loot, or regents.  This is really rare though.  Seems to be only Paladins that do this too.<br>
<br>
Angeyl D`Elghinn<br>
Teir'Dal Priestess of Innoruuk<br>
<br>
p.s. would I symbol the Chanter at my level? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/14/00 12:56:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buffing</span><hr size=1> Because enchanters are fragile.<br>
<br>
Let's say you're fighting in a group outside Paw.  What's 1.2pp per cycle?  FS drops like candy, pick some up.  Or better yet, get someone to master loot.  Monks tend to like that kinda thing too. <p><hr>
