<font face="Arial" size="2">M</font><font face="Arial" size="1">ASTER BOOZER, BAITER, SINGER, AND PLAYER</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uinyxdater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inyx DAter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/14/00 1:14:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buffing</span><hr size=1> Staggering buffs is a good idea.  Dispells are a PAIN because they mess up your rhythm.  Otherwise splitting the buffs and synchronizing them is great.<br>
<br>
If the enchanter is doing a lot of mezzing and the tanks are being slow about pulling it off of him/her, yes by ALL means symbol them.<br>
<br>
Without a chanter the real big problem is keeping up with mana demand.  At times you will be forced to put your valor series hp/ac buff on everyone and armor series only on you and the tanks.  Still symbol the tank if the extra hps would help.<br>
<br>
Personally, I feel that to cast symbol on the tanks before you can cast CH and they have 1500 hps is probably unnecessary.  You still have to heal them with heals that won't see any benefit to the higher maximum.  <br>
<br>
So, at this level, I would personally just hold off on the symbol unless there is a great risk of quick hp drop or in the case of a low hp caster who is getting unwanted attention.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><HR>
