<FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="BLUE"><B>Lanys T'vyl</B></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udragon257.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dragon257</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.fortunecity.com/dragon257/10ank.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/14/00 2:23:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buffing</span><hr size=1> Hmm, you gave me an Idea I want to try...<br>
<br>
What if I symbol buff myself, and the Enchanter, and leave mr 1300hps alone... That saves the reagents needed, and still serves the purpose of allowing our delicate classes the extra HPS to live long enough to receive a Greater Heal (thus agroing them on me, which is no big deal since I can go Devine...)<br>
<br>
I may have to experiment with that one. But I do know that the Symbol Buff on our main tank saved our parties life durin Sunday's Raid on Unrest. If he hadn't had it, he would have been dead when my G-Heal went off... Wasting 150 mana on a corpse is no fun, and not to mention the 4 MOBs be had kept taunted on himself would have frenzied either me or the other Cleric...<br>
<br>
But with his Symbol, Tylor lived, got a G-Heal at less than 1/2 bubble of health (about 150 hps) and promptly kicked the living snot out of the undead in the Bar room and the Tower. (He had gone beserk, and since the heal was for about a bubble each, two G-Heals still left him Beserk... A beserk Barbarian with an Exe. Axe... oh the inhumaity!) <p><center><strong>
~Damahn Amungmehn</strong><br>
Cleric of the 30th Cross<br>
Web Master, Founding Officer<br>
<a href="http://members.fortunecity.com/dragon257">
Dragons Protectorate</a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucamdarlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CamdarLanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/15/00 8:01:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buffing</span><hr size=1> Costs of a Cleric.  <br>
<br>
The cleric is probably the poorest class in the game, always has been.  Between our Armor, Spells and Regeants we seem perpetually broke until the higher levels.  Don't expect it to get any less expensive later on, but the loot is generally so good that it hardly matters.  If you are a mid-level cleric, either demand a ML situation or have someone loot for you.  Either way works well, just explain it to the group.  Few people understand regeant costs unless you explain them.<br>
<br>
To give you an idea of how buffing and the expences for them go I will show you how I do it and what it costs.<br>
<br>
I try each day to refill my regeant BP.  In it I keep 80 Jasper, 40 Peridots, and 40 Pearls.  <br>
<br>
I keep 3 buffs up at all times on all members.  Symbol, Marzim for the Tanks (peridot), Pinzarm for all others (Jasper).  I keep Armor of Faith (free cast with my gauntlets) on all members at all times.  I also keep the entire group with Heroism (easier now with group hero).  If we are fighting a named mob or we are breaking a new area I also keep Death Pact (Pearl) on all members.  So if you do the math on a break this is the cost:<br>
<br>
Peridot X 3 = 33 pp<br>
Jasper X 3 = 3 pp<br>
Pearl X 6 = 30 pp<br>
<br>
So roughly 66pp per cycle during named or break and then 36pp per cycle afterwards.  I generally go through 200-300 pp per night just in buffs.  If you explain this to your group, then they are generally more then generous with any money items/cash that drops.<br>
<br>
Symbol is probably the most important and least used buff we have.  Symbol becomes even more important later when you start using CHeal.  Always keep your primary tanks, your chanter and yourself with symbol.  Always keep your entire group with the Valor/Reso/Hero line.  Always keep your Tanks, Chanter, and yourself buffed with your Guard/Armor of Faith/Shield of Words line.  If you do this on a regular basis you will find that you are healing much less and actually have much more mana in the long run.  <br>
<br>
Just a few random thoughts on buffs, <br>
<br>
I wish each of you the best of luck,<br>
<br>
I am,<br>
<br>
Camdar Sol'Dara<br>
55 Templar <br>
